	<p>
		<div>Aalto Global Impact brings together inspirational speakers from business, civil society and academia. Key topics tackle mitigating problems of runaway urbanization, transforming existing business models, promoting social entrepreneurship and building competencies for a sustainable future.</div><div>&nbsp;<br></div><div>The speakers include Mugendi M’Rithaa, Professor of Industrial Design (Cape Peninsula University of Technology, South Africa), Tim N’Dezi, Director of Centre for Community Initiatives (Tanzania), representatives from Finnish companies and Creative Sustainability students from Aalto University.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>The event is hosted by Aalto Global Impact &nbsp;together&nbsp;with Master’s Degree Programme in Creative Sustainability and moderated by Alastair Fuad-Luke, Professor of Emerging Design Practices from School of Arts, Design and Architecture.</div><div><br></div><div>14.00 &nbsp;Welcome</div><div><br></div><div>14.10 &nbsp;Aalto Global Impact presentation</div><div><br></div><div>14.20-14.50 Mitigating Problems of Runaway Urbanization</div><div><br></div><div><ul><li>Professor Mugendi M’Rithaa, Cape Peninsula University of Technology, South Africa&nbsp;<br></li><li>Water and sanitation expert, Sustainable Global Technologies&nbsp;<br></li><li>City in Transition student&nbsp;<br></li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>14.50-15.50 Building Competencies for Societal Visionaries&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><ul><li>Helena Sandman, Architect/Teacher, City in Transition, Aalto University<br></li><li>Björn Pehrson, Professor, KTH Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm, Sweden&nbsp;<br></li><li>Director Tim N’Dezi, Centre for Community Initiatives, Dar es Salaam, Tanzania&nbsp;<br></li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>Creative Sustainability presentation</div><div><br></div><div>15.50-16.10 Break</div><div><br></div><div>16.10-16.40 Transforming existing Business Models</div><div><br></div><div><ul><li>Hannamaija Fontell, Director R&amp;D, Biolan Oy&nbsp;<br></li><li>Tiina Saukko, CEO, World Vision Finland<br></li><li>Jusa Susia, Director, Finpro&nbsp;<br></li><li>Henna Husso, MSc Candidate, Aalto School of Business<br></li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>16.40-17.10 Social Innovation and Entrepreneurship&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><ul><li>Frank-Martin Belz, Professor, University of Technology, Munich&nbsp;<br></li><li>Eeva Houtbeckers, PhD Candidate, Aalto School of Business&nbsp;<br></li><li>Tommi Rimpiläinen, Entrepreneur/ Weego (TBC)<br></li></ul></div><div><br></div><div>17.10-17.30 Discussions</div><div><br></div><div><b>Place:</b> MoA, Hämeentie 39</div><div><br></div><div><b>Please regieter a</b>t:&nbsp;<a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dGVxZXVnN01fU2VWak9ubmdacndJLVE6MA" title="Web registration" target="_blank">https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dGVxZXVnN01fU2VWak9ubmdacndJLVE6MA</a></div><div><br></div><div>To find more information about MOA please visit:&nbsp;</div><div><a href="http://moa.aalto.fi/2013/en/" title="MOA" target="_blank">http://moa.aalto.fi/2013/en/</a></div><div><br></div>
